ver correlations and anti-correlations between the four indices. We\ndiscuss the physical basis of those correlations. As it turns out, the\n\"photospheric\" indices appear to be most strongly affected by continuum\nemission. We thus anticipate that these indices may prove to be useful proxies\nfor monitoring continuum emission in the near ultraviolet.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 1 Nov 2015 17:34:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-23"}
